<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 13 at 5:28PM EDT  by NWS Cleveland</headline>
<description>...A line of snow showers will affect northeastern Portage...
Trumbull...eastern Mahoning...Geauga...northern Cuyahoga...Lake and
Ashtabula Counties Until 700 PM EDT....
At 527 PM EDT, radar indicated snow showers along a line extending
from 6 miles north of Lakewood to near West Farmington to near
Campbell, moving east at 25 mph.
HAZARDS INCLUDE...
Visibility dropping to less than three quarters of a mile...
Locations impacted include...
Cleveland, Youngstown, Warren, Painesville, Ashtabula, Willowick,
Conneaut, Chardon, Fairport Harbor, Geneva-On-The-Lake, Lakewood,
Euclid, Mentor, Cleveland Heights, Boardman, Solon, Willoughby,
Niles, Eastlake and Warrensville Heights.
Use extra caution if you must travel. Rapid changes in visibility
may lead to accidents.</description>
